 The individual fragments are copies of the corresponding 'Master' fragments defined on the fragment files.
 However, they may have been rotated (and translated) with respect to the Master. The local coordinate axes
 of each fragment (which define for instance the spatial orientation in the current molecule of a fragment
 P:x orbital) are not necessarily those of the molecule.
 The local frame (if different from the molecular one) is printed to enable an interpretation of the expan-
 sion of an MO in Fragment Orbitals.



